          "164196 university students",
          "10430 courses at University of California Berkeley",
          "Student’s personal course history,\nCourse Pre-Requisites embeddings\n",
          "0/random initialization since there is no history when student registers.",
          "Updates are done via update to the LSTM weights based on how the learner evolves throughout the courses.",
          "Authors filtered the dataset to e exclusively account for records from Fall 2016 to recommend courses for Spring 2016.\n\nCourse history is encoded in the form of embeddings.\n\n ",
          "Top-10 Course Recommendations - computed and sorted in descending order  by the probability of achieving an A.",
          "{Accuracy: 0.5765 - Model 2 on B Treshold}",
          "Authors do a complete work that follows a sequence of different steps: \n\n1. There is a prediction of course performance, which is enhanced by a prediction of performance in a using information from pre-requisite courses.\n\n2. The LMSTM predicts the probability of achieving an A for every available course in the following semester and recommends the 10 in which the poorobability is highest.\n\nSince this is a backtest, authors consider a successful reccomendation if the student took a course that is listed in the top-10 recommendations list.",
          "Recommender only takes into account courses taken in previous semester. May benefit from working with a longer sequence.\n\nImbalanced dataset."
        ]
